## Methodological Lessons

### What This Project Did Right

✅ **Tested the hard thing:** Out-of-distribution generalization, not just in-distribution accuracy  
✅ **Reported negative result honestly:** Could have published Phases 2–8 as perfect metrics; instead framed as memorization diagnostic  
✅ **Used established best practices:** Apollo-standard methodology (train-easy-test-hard, AUROC metrics, FPR thresholds)  
✅ **Full reproducibility:** Fixed seeds, Colab notebooks, clean code, minimal dependencies  
✅ **Clear interpretation:** Explicitly reframed perfect metrics as warning signs, not validation  

### What Could Have Been Better

⚠️ **Started with larger N:** N=10 was always going to be an overfitting regime; starting with N≥100 would have saved Phases 4–8  
⚠️ **Aligned with benchmarks earlier:** Use WMDP-Bio in Phase 3 instead of only Phase 9  
⚠️ **Cross-architecture testing:** Skipped due to compute; should have been Phase 7 priority  

